ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Form used/assessment name
Notes: e.g., Self-Report, Parent Form, Short Form, Revised Version

ElementDescription: Respondent
Notes: NA=Not Applicable

ElementDescription: Ohio unhealthy behavior total score
Notes: Sum of ohio_unhealth_behav_q1 to ohio_unhealth_behav_q20

ElementDescription: Overall, how satisfied are you with your relationship with your child right now?
Notes: 1=Extremely satisfied; 2=Moderately satisfied; 3=Somewhat satisfied; 4=Somewhat dissatisfied; 5=Moderately dissatisfied; 6=Extremely dissatisfied

ElementDescription: How capable of dealing with your child's problems do you feel right now?
Notes: 1=Extremely capable; 2=Moderately capable; 3=Somewhat capable; 4=Somewhat incapable; 5=Moderately incapable; 6=Extremely incapable

ElementDescription: How much stress or pressure is in your life right now?
Notes: 1=Very little; 2=Some; 3=Quite a bit; 4=A moderate amount; 5=A great deal; 6=Unbearable amounts

ElementDescription: How optimistic are you about your child's future right now?
Notes: 1=The future looks very bright; 2=The future looks somewhat bright; 3=The future looks OK; 4=The future looks both good and bad; 5=The future looks bad; 6=The future looks very bad

ElementDescription: How satisfied are you with the mental health services your child has received so far?
Notes: 1=Extremely satisfied; 2=Moderately satisfied; 3=Somewhat satisfied; 4=Somewhat dissatisfied; 5=Moderately dissatisfied; 6=Extremely dissatisfied

ElementDescription: To what degree have you been included in the treatment planning process for your child?
Notes: 1=A great deal; 2=Moderately; 3=Quite a bit; 4=Somewhat; 5=A little; 6=Not at all

ElementDescription: Mental health workers involved in my case listen to and value my ideas about treatment planning for my child.
Notes: 1=A great deal; 2=Moderately; 3=Quite a bit; 4=Somewhat; 5=A little; 6=Not at all

ElementDescription: To what extent does your child's treatment plan include your ideas about your child's treatment needs?
